OL,3,CHow Talking Street Signs are keeping
OL,4,Can island language alive
OL,6,FThe signs have been placed at 15
OL,7,Fhistoric landmarks in the town.
OL,9,FEach has a QR code that, once scanned,
OL,10,Freads snippets of St Helier's history
OL,11,Fin Jerriais with a translation
OL,12,Fprovided in English.
OL,14,FMature students learning with L'Office
OL,15,Fdu Jerriais, who teach the language in
OL,16,Fschools and online, devised the
OL,17,Fproject.
OL,19,FStudent, Laurence Curtis said the
OL,20,Foriginal idea came when tourists asked
OL,21,Fif he spoke the language.
