OL,3,CHow Talking Street Signs are keeping
OL,4,Can island language alive
OL,6,FHe explained: "Two visitors from
OL,7,FNormandy who needed directions in town
OL,8,Fasked me if I spoke Jerriais as they
OL,9,Fwanted to hear and record it.
OL,11,F"That gave me the idea to look for
OL,12,Fways to make it easier for people to
OL,13,Fhear Jerriais around the Island, as
OL,14,Fwell as being able to see it."
OL,16,FIt is hoped that the signs will make
OL,17,Fthe language more accessible to
OL,18,Fvisitors and islanders.
